.TH CAGE 1 "June 2026" "cage" "Cage Manual"
.SH NAME
cage \- minimal age-backed 1Password environment secret manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cage
[--config PATH] [--verbose] COMMAND [ARGS]
.PP
.B cage get
[--profiles LIST] [--environments LIST] [--json] ENV_VAR|*
.PP
.B cage exec
[--profiles LIST] [--environments LIST] -- COMMAND [ARG...]
.PP
.B cage environment
create|list|delete ...
.PP
.B cage profile
create|list|delete ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cage
loads 1Password Environments using age-protected 1Password service account tokens.
It is macOS-only and uses a single global config file at
.BR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/cage/config.toml ,
falling back to
.BR ~/.config/cage/config.toml .
Set
.B CAGE_CONFIG
or pass
.B --config PATH
to use another config; the flag takes precedence.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Relative identity and provider files are resolved from the config file directory.
Supported identity types are
.BR basic ,
.BR yubikey ,
and
.BR secure-enclave .
Supported provider type is
.BR 1password .
Supported environment type is
.BR 1password-environment .
.SH RESOLUTION
Profiles and environments are selected with comma-separated
.B --profiles
and
.B --environments
flags, or with
.B CAGE_PROFILES
and
.BR CAGE_ENVIRONMENTS .
Flags override environment variables. Profiles load first in order, then explicit environments. Last loaded variable wins. There is no default profile.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B cage identity basic create NAME
Create a native age identity, write
.BR NAME.identity
with mode 0600, and update config.
.TP
.B cage identity yubikey create NAME
Create a YubiKey identity, write
.BR NAME.identity
with mode 0600, and update config.
.TP
.B cage identity se create NAME
Create a Secure Enclave identity, write
.BR NAME.identity
with mode 0600, and update config.
.TP
.B cage provider 1p create NAME --identity IDENTITY
Read a 1Password service account token securely or from stdin, encrypt it to one identity, write
.BR NAME.1p.age
with mode 0600, and update config.
.TP
.B cage environment create NAME --provider PROVIDER --uuid UUID
Create a 1Password Environment config entry.
.TP
.B cage environment list
List configured environments.
.TP
.B cage environment delete NAME
Delete an environment config entry if no profile references it.
.TP
.B cage profile create NAME --environments ENV[,ENV...]
Create a flat profile from configured environments.
.TP
.B cage profile list
List configured profiles.
.TP
.B cage profile delete NAME
Delete a profile.
.TP
.B cage get ENV_VAR
Print a single resolved value. Missing variables exit with status 1.
.TP
.B cage get '*'
Print all resolved variables as KEY=value lines. Use
.B --json
for a JSON object.
.TP
.B cage exec -- COMMAND
Replace cage with COMMAND where supported, inheriting the parent environment overlaid with resolved variables. OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN is removed from the child environment.
.TP
.B cage completion SHELL
Generate shell completions for bash, zsh, fish, or powershell.
.TP
.B cage man DIR
Generate full roff manpages for cage and subcommands.
.SH SECURITY NOTES
Provider tokens are decrypted only in memory to initialize the 1Password SDK. 1Password Environments are not cached on disk or across loads. cage redacts common secret-looking values in errors.
